    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Barge-like, flat-bottomed sailing ships common to the Netherlands from the Middle Ages to the end of the 19th century, used for fishing and river and costal transport.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
